<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLARKE TAYLOR; FORMER TIMES THEATER CRITIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Clarke Taylor, 46, a New York-based critic for this newspaper who wrote for 
both the daily and Sunday Calendar sections from 1978 to 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Taylor was a founding member of the Performing Artists for Nuclear Disarmament, 
the AIDS Medical Foundation, the American Foundation for AIDS Research and 
other fund-raising and AIDS-support groups. He once was an English and drama 
teacher in Baltimore and New York City. On Jan. 5 in a Manhattan hospital of 
the complications of acquired immune deficiency syndrome. 
</P>
</TEXT>
