<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
COLD-SHOOTING USC LOSES 7TH IN A ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Arizona women's basketball team handed cold-shooting USC its seventh 
consecutive loss Thursday night, defeating the Trojans, 58-53, in a Pacific 10 
Conference game in Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
Although the Trojans shot only 32%, they got 16 points from senior guard Tammy 
Hammond while Rosalind Hodge had 17 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
USC falls to 0-2 in conference play and 2-7 overall. Arizona is 1-2 in 
conference play and 8-6 overall. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA 77, Arizona State 67 -- Behind a career-high 22 points from freshman point 
guard Nicole Anderson, the Bruins won their third consecutive game in defeating 
the Sun Devils in Tempe. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore guard DeDe Mosman had a career-high 17 points for UCLA. Fran Ciak led 
Arizona State with 24 points. UCLA is 2-0 in conference play and 7-5 overall. 
The Sun Devils are 0-3 and 8-5. 
</P>
