</P>
<P>
ANTELOPE VALLEY TO HOLD SERVICE FOR SANFORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A memorial service for Antelope Valley High senior Chris Sanford, who was 
killed last Saturday night when he was struck by a stray bullet that police 
believe was fired by a gang member, is scheduled today at 11:30 a.m. at the 
school's football field. The funeral is scheduled for 4 p.m. Saturday at 
Lancaster Baptist Church. 
</P>
<P>
Sanford, the goalkeeper for the Antelopes' soccer team, was shot in the right 
eye after a fight broke out at a party he was attending in Lancaster, police 
said. Authorities continue to look for a 16- to 18-year-old Latino male 
believed to be the member of a San Fernando Valley gang. 
</P>
<P>
Rich Hill, Cal Lutheran's baseball coach, has been selected head coach of the 
Chatham A's in the Cape Cod League, one of the nation's top summer leagues for 
college-level players. 
</P>
<P>
The Cape Cod League season runs from June until August. Hill was an assistant 
coach for the Brewster Whitecaps last season. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff deLaveaga of Cal Lutheran is ranked 19th in National Assn. Intercollegiate 
Athletics scoring, averaging 26.7 points a game. Greg Sutton of Oral Roberts 
ranks first with a 41.7 average. 
</P>
<P>
DeLaveaga, a sophomore guard, is also the second leading scorer in District 3. 
</P>
<P>
Greg Maw, a senior kicker for the Cal Lutheran football team, has been named a 
second-team Academic All-American. Maw, a political science major with a 3.83 
grade-point average, led the Kingsmen in scoring last season. He kicked six 
field goals and 14 extra points. 
</P>
<P>
The Cal State Northridge track and field coaching staff will hold a free 
learn-by-doing clinic from 9:30 to 11:30 on Saturday morning. 
</P>
<P>
The clinic will be held before an all-comers meet at CSUN starting at noon. 
Northridge Coach Don Strametz and assistants Tony Veney, Bob Augello, Tim 
Werner and Dan Lange will be on hand. 
</P>
<P>
Softball sign-ups for the Sylmar Independent League, for girls aged 7 to 18, 
will be held from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m. on the weekends of Jan. 13-14, 20-21 and 
27-28. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 818-365-2436. 
</P>
<P>
A ceremony sponsored by the Mid-Valley Baseball Assn. will be held at noon Feb. 
4 to dedicate a baseball field in the name of Brett Saberhagen. 
</P>
<P>
Saberhagen, a Cleveland High graduate and two-time Cy Young Award winner for 
the Kansas City Royals, will be present. 
</P>
<P>
A celebrity softball game will be held after the ceremony. 
</P>
<P>
The field is located at the corner of Oxnard Street and Louise Avenue in 
Encino. 
</P>
<P>
Information: 818-344-2657. 
</P>
