<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOME THOUGHTS ON UNTRASHING L.A. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I enjoyed the article regarding the highly respected waste organizer, Joan 
Edwards, hired by L.A. City to reduce the voluminous mountains of trash 
currently dumped into the landfills. 
</P>
<P>
I hope she is able to bring about discipline to our disposable society. 
</P>
<P>
I also hope she can bring about some change in the bottled drink industry. It 
bothers me that only the beer and soda companies have a deposit/return system 
to encourage recycling, while the juice industry, with those heavy, valuable 
glass bottles, offers no incentive at all. 
</P>
<P>
I support Joan Edwards' ideals and trust that her office will remain free of 
special interests. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD WRIGHT, Rowland Heights 
</P>
</TEXT>
