<P>
LASER INSTITUTE GETS $6.2 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UC Irvine Beckman Laser Institute received the largest single contribution 
in the university's history as the Arnold and Mabel Beckman Foundation of 
Corona del Mar presented the medical clinic with $6.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
The donation launches a campus-wide campaign that officials hope will bring in 
more than $200 million over the next few years. "This gift is most exciting 
because it assures the institute the funding necessary to remain at the 
forefront of laser biomedicine," said Dr. Michael Berns, the institute's 
director and co-founder. About $5.2 million of the donation will go toward the 
institute's research endowment, while the rest will complete a pledge made last 
year by the Beckman foundation to support new research positions. 
</P>
