<P>
3 DIE, 3 HURT WHEN PICKUP STRIKES SIDE OF CLIFF ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pickup struck the side of a cliff on the Antelope Valley Freeway near Agua 
Dulce on Thursday, killing three passengers and injuring three others, the 
California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
The dead, who were riding in the bed of the pickup, were thrown onto the 
roadway, Officer Wendy Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
Another passenger thrown from the truck bed suffered major injuries and was 
taken by helicopter to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital in Valencia, Moore 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver appeared to have been under the influence of alcohol, Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
Authorities said the truck appeared to have rolled several times, littering the 
pavement with debris. 
</P>
<P>
No other vehicles were involved, and there were no witnesses, Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver and a passenger in the truck cab were being treated at Palmdale 
Hospital Medical Center for moderate injuries, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The names of the dead and injured were not immediately available. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred about 8:30 p.m. just south of the Escondido Canyon Road 
on-ramp, on the southbound side of the freeway, authorities said. 
</P>
