<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIG BUCKS: Arnold O. Beckman's deep pockets foundation, which is giving $6.2 
million to the UC Irvine laser institute that bears his name (B7), operates on 
a vest pocket budget. . . . The $200-million foundation told the IRS in 1988 it 
gave away $47 million, mostly to scientific and medical projects, with no 
full-time staff and a payroll under $10,000. Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BECKMAN LASER INSTITUTE; ARNOLD AND MABEL BECKMAN FOUNDATION; UNIVERSITY OF 
CALIFORNIA AT IRVINE; GRANTS; PHILANTHROPY; FINANCIAL DISCLOSURE 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
