ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
EISNER GRILLED: Thursday's Disneyland press conference was supposed to be 
nostalgic (B6), but from the media ranks came a barbed question: Won't new 
admission prices ($25.50 for adults, up 8.5%) keep families away? . . . The 
question came from Samantha Test, 11, of La Palma, "cub" reporter for the 
Irvine-based Bear Essential News for Kids and caught Disney CEO Michael Eisner 
by surprise. "That's the toughest question I've had in a year," he said with a 
small laugh, then explained that surveys show patrons will pay the price. Mark 
I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
