<HEADLINE>
<P>
COACH PULLS TEAM OFF COURT AFTER DISPUTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Capistrano Valley Christian High School was awarded a forfeit over Brethren 
Thursday when the Olympic League girls' basketball game was stopped after the 
Brethren team was pulled from the court by its coach in a dispute over 
officiating. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley Christian led, 37-19, when the game was stopped at the end of 
the third quarter. The Brethren coach was called for a technical foul in the 
second quarter and another in the third. She was ejected for arguing with the 
referee, according to Tim Shelton, Capistrano Valley Christian coach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
