<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT / COMMERCIAL REAL ESTATE: FOCUS: MACARTHUR PLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction has begun on the first office building in the $1-billion MacArthur 
Place development in Santa Ana. The 11-story limestone and polished granite 
building, a project of BCE Development Inc., will be joined later by twin 
seven-story Gateway Buildings, a five-story structure and two 20-story towers. 
</P>
<P>
They will form a quadrangle along the main entry into the complex. MacArthur 
Place, located within Santa Ana's redevelopment area, will also have 
residential, hotel and retail areas, as well as a three-acre water garden and a 
park within its 66 acres. The project is scheduled for completion in 10 to 15 
years. 
</P>
<P>
FACTS AND FIGURES 
</P>
<P>
Address: Northeastern corner of Main St. and MacArthur Blvd., Santa Ana 
</P>
<P>
Developer: BCE Development Inc., a subsidiary of Bell Canada Enterprises 
</P>
<P>
Architect: Gensler and Associates 
</P>
<P>
Builder: Austin Co. 
</P>
<P>
Number of floors: 11 
</P>
<P>
Square feet: 250,000 
</P>
<P>
Use: Office 
</P>
<P>
Cost: $50 million 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled completion date Early 1991 
</P>
<P>
Percentage of building leased 50% pre-leased 
</P>
<P>
Parking capacity 750 underground, plus surface parking 
</P>
<P>
Source: Ralph Jackson Associates Inc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
