<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEIGHT AND WEIGHT CHART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To find out if you are the recommended weight for your height, consult the 
following guide. The weight is in pounds with clothes on, the height is with 
shoes (1-inch heels). 
</P>
<P>
HOW TO DETERMINE FRAME SIZE 
</P>
<P>
To determine your frame size, extend your arm and bend the forearm up at a 
90-degree angle. Keep fingers straight and turn the inside of your wrist toward 
your body. Place thumb and index finger of your other hand on the two prominent 
bones on each side of your elbow. Measure the space between your fingers 
against a ruler or tape measure. Compare it with the following guide for 
medium-framed men and women. If the measurement is less than that stated here, 
you have a small frame; if it is more, you have a large frame: 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
For men -- 
</P>
<P>
5 feet, 2 inches-5 feet, 4 inches 2 1/2 to 2 7/8 inches 
</P>
<P>
5 feet, 5 inches-5 feet, 7 inches 2 5/8 to 2 7/8 inches 
</P>
<P>
5 feet, 8 inches-5 feet, 11 inches 2 3/4 to 3 inches 
</P>
<P>
6 feet-6 feet, 3 inches 2 3/4 to 3 1/8 inches 
</P>
<P>
6 feet, 4 inches 2 7/8 to 3 1/4 inches 
</P>
<P>
For women -- 
</P>
<P>
4 feet, 10 inches-5 feet, 3 inches 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 inches 
</P>
<P>
5 feet, 4 inches-5 feet, 11 inches 2 3/8 to 2 5/8 inches 
</P>
<P>
6 feet and taller 2 1/2 to 2 3/4 inches 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
MALE 
</P>
