<HEADLINE>
<P>
P. M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
PICKENS SUES FIRM IN TOKYO COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
T. Boone Pickens is carrying his Japanese corporate battle to court with a 
lawsuit to gain access to the financial books of Koito Manufacturing Co. Ltd., 
the auto parts maker of which he is the largest shareholder, Pickens' lawyer 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Pickens filed the lawsuit in Tokyo District Court, his lawyer, Kanji Ishizumi, 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that Pickens will win. But it is all up to the judges," 
Ishizumi said. 
</P>
<P>
Koito has not agreed to Pickens' request for the right to look over its account 
books covering the years from April 1, 1979, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Koito told Pickens to wait until Jan. 22 for a response, Ishizumi said. "But 
there is no reason why we have to wait that long," he added. 
</P>
<P>
Pickens holds a 26% stake in Koito through his private investment firm Boone 
Co. Toyota Motor Corp. holds 19% of Koito's shares, buys the bulk of its 
output, and has three seats on its board. Pickens has been denied any seats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
