<P>
CHINA EYES DEVALUATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's central bank, after devaluing the currency by 21.2% last month, is 
considering another devaluation of about 10%, banking sources said today. 
</P>
<P>
They said no decision had been reached, but a steep fall in inflation has 
emboldened central bankers who now believe that a second move on the renminbi 
would not risk a serious rise in prices. 
</P>
