<P>
ROUNDTREE JOINS 'GENERATIONS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Richard Roundtree, best known for the "Shaft" movies, will join the cast of 
NBC's daytime drama, "Generations," as a doctor. The announcement was made 
today by Brandon Tartikoff, president of NBC Entertainment, at the network's 
semi-annual press gathering in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Roundtree will star as Daniel Reubens, a doctor forced to live in hiding for 
the past 15 years after being blamed for a murder he did not commit. He will 
make his first on-air appearance Jan. 22. 
</P>
<P>
Roundtree starred as John Shaft in a trio of movies about the private eye: 
"Shaft," "Shaft's Big Score" and "Shaft In Africa." He also starred in a 
90-minute television version, "Shaft." 
</P>
<P>
Tartikoff said the addition of Roundtree is "further indication of our 
commitment to and confidence" in "Generations," which debuted last year. 
</P>
