<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
UCLA PICKS UP DEFENSIVE COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jacob Burney, who coached the defensive line at the University of Wisconsin 
last year, has joined the UCLA football staff in the same capacity, the school 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
Burney coached the inside linebackers at Mississippi State in 1988 and took a 
job at the University of South Carolina in January, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
A month later, after the death of head coach Joe Morrison, Burney joined the 
Wisconsin staff. 
</P>
<P>
Burney was a four-year starter in the defensive line at Tennessee-Chattanooga, 
from which he graduated in 1981. He began his coaching career at New Mexico in 
1983, where he coached the defensive line for four years. 
</P>
<P>
He then spent one year at the University of Tulsa, where he coached the 
defensive line, before moving to Mississippi State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
